    },
    "Syncing article content increases iCloud storage use, sync time, and battery use.\n\nArticle status and the content of starred articles are always synced." : {
      "localizations" : {
        "zh-Hans" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "同步文章内容会增加 iCloud 存储占用、同步时间和耗电量。\n\n文章的已读状态、以及加星标文章的内容,始终都会同步。"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "System Default (%@)" : {
      "comment" : "Default browser item title format",
      "localizations" : {
        "zh-Hans" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "系统默认(%@)"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "Thanks to Sheila and my family; thanks to my friends in Seattle and around the globe; thanks to the ever-patient and ever-awesome NetNewsWire beta testers.\n\nThanks to [Gus Mueller](https://shapeof.com/) for [FMDB](https://github.com/ccgus/fmdb) by [Flying Meat Software](http://flyingmeat.com/). Thanks to [GitHub](https://github.com) and [Discourse](https://discourse.com) for making open source collaboration easy and fun. Thanks to [Ben Ubois](https://benubois.com/) at [Feedbin](https://feedbin.com) for all the extra help with syncing and article rendering — and [for hosting the server for the Reader view](https://feedbin.com/blog/2019/03/11/the-future-of-full-content/)." : {
      "comment" : "A list of credits for the app.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true,
      "localizations" : {
        "zh-Hans" : {
          "stringUnit" : {
            "state" : "translated",
            "value" : "感谢 Sheila 和我的家人;感谢我在西雅图和世界各地的朋友;感谢始终耐心、始终出色的 NetNewsWire 测试者们。\n\n感谢 [Gus Mueller](https://shapeof.com/) 带来 [Flying Meat Software](http://flyingmeat.com/) 的 [FMDB](https://github.com/ccgus/fmdb)。感谢 [GitHub](https://github.com) 和 [Discourse](https://discourse.com) 让开源协作变得轻松而有趣。感谢 [Feedbin](https://feedbin.com) 的 [Ben Ubois](https://benubois.com/) 在同步和文章渲染上给予的额外帮助 —— 以及[为阅读视图提供服务器托管](https://feedbin.com/blog/2019/03/11/the-future-of-full-content/)。"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "The name can be anything you want. You can even use emoji. 🎸" : {
